diff:1619323146:1619323146:=1,54d0%0a%3c :Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a%3c :Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a%3c :Title: Canadian French Discrimination%0a%3c :Author: CharlieP%0a%3c :Section: D%0a%3c :Completed: 24.04.2021 - 20:59%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c Summary: \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Canadian French Discrimination against citizens and Justin Trudeau%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Overall, French is a very prescriptive language and is often overlooked by a governing body, which decides what is "proper" French and "improper" French. Quebecois French is often seen as "improper" French by those outside Canada, and in the past, sometimes by "proper" French speakers inside Canada. However, as Quebec and Quebecois French have grown, and with the creation of "Standard Quebecois French," there is increasing discrimination against both Parisian Francophones and French-speaking Anglophones. The intension with this standardization is to protect the dialect and prevent it from being influenced by French-speaking immigrants, but this same attitude has lead to exclusion and ridicule of Canadian citizens.%0a%3c %0a%3c One example is that of Justin Trudeau, the Prime Minister of Canada. Despite Trudeau's fluency in French, he is often made fun of for not using "proper" Quebecois French. For example, Huffington Post Quebec stated that he "utters sentences that would not be normal for a Francophone." In addition, Le Devoir published an article, "When our elected officials mangle our language," as well as instructions on normative phonetics for Quebecois French.  %0a%3c %0a%3c In this Radio Canada video:%0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VqBo7-dtLJA %0a%3c %0a%3c Justin Trudeau and many other Canadian citizens speak about the discomfort they feel as Francophones and Anglophones trying to fit into the Quebecois community. Many people in this video feel as if they are being marginalized or associated with incorrect groups due to their "incorrect" French usage. %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
